detail_description: Alibag Magnetic Observatory, the second oldest magnetic observatory in India following Culaba, has been recording Earth's magnetic observations since 1860. The facility boasts a diverse collection of magnetometers for continuous monitoring, making it one of the few observatories worldwide with such an extensive array of magnetic records and instruments. Established by the Indian Institute of Geomagnetism in 1904, access to the premises has been restricted and security tightened since 26/11.
name: Alibag Magnetic Observatory
address: JVW9+3VR, Police Line, Alibag, Maharashtra 402201, India
